Fix DEG/EG and RS annexure mapping AND expand RS Excel classifier to accept
common single-strength / injection composition formats. Both mappers have the
same architectural defect: they only work when the material is in a hardcoded
family alias vocabulary. Anything outside that vocabulary silently fails.
Product-agnostic identity resolution must work for ANY molecule, without
requiring pre-registration.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PART A — MAPPER FIX (applies to BOTH DEG/EG AND RS)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Bug evidence (DEG/EG mapper, confirmed):
- Croscarmellose Sodium ↔ Croscarmellose Sodium (identical strings) → No match
- Mavacamten IH Spec 1 ↔ MAVACAMTEN (in candidates) → No match
- Mannitol (Pearlitol 50C) ↔ Pearlitol Mannitol Powder → No match
- Hypromellose ↔ Methocel → Auto-accepted (family alias hit)
- Magnesium Stearate ↔ Magnesium Stearate NF → Auto-accepted (family alias hit)
- Aerosil ↔ AEROSIL 200 → Low-confidence match (family alias hit)

RS mapper: assume same defect exists. If present, apply the same fix. Check
by running an internal test with composition="Croscarmellose Sodium" and
annexure material_name="Croscarmellose Sodium". If the mapper returns No
match, the fix below is required.

Pattern: mapper only works when both sides hit a hardcoded family alias.
Token-matching fallback path is broken. Any new molecule outside the family
vocabulary silently fails. This is unacceptable for a product-agnostic
platform.

Required mapper fixes (apply to both deg_eg.py and residual_solvent.py):

1. Remove any family-gate that returns 0 when both sides lack a family alias.
   Even without a family, token-based scoring MUST run and produce a real score.

2. Build annexure identity pool from ALL of these sources, not just
   material_name:
   - material_name (highest weight)
   - each entry in material_name_candidates (equal weight to material_name)
   - filename after stripping annexure numbers, SAP codes, dates, extensions
   - document_title (only when material_name and candidates are empty)
   - supplier_name (weak evidence only)

3. Exact normalized match must auto-accept at confidence 0.99, regardless of
   family status. Normalize by:
   - lowercase
   - strip parenthesized brand descriptors and preserve inside content as
     tokens (e.g. "Mannitol (Pearlitol 50C)" tokens: mannitol, pearlitol, 50c)
   - strip specification/grade/pharmacopoeia suffixes: "IH Spec 1", "Spec 1",
     "Specification", "Grade", "USP", "NF", "Ph Eur", "EP", "JP", "IP", "BP",
     "CoA", "Certificate of Analysis"
   - strip punctuation, normalize whitespace
   Then compare token sets:
   - normalized(composition) == normalized(annexure_material_name) → 0.99
   - normalized(composition) == normalized(any candidate) → 0.99
   - normalized(composition) == normalized(filename_derived_name) → 0.95

4. Token containment fallback: if composition's distinctive tokens are a
   subset of the annexure identity pool tokens (or vice versa), return 0.90.
   Example: "Croscarmellose Sodium" tokens {croscarmellose, sodium} contained
   in annexure pool {croscarmellose, sodium, ac, di, sol, sd, 711} → 0.90.

5. Reduce noise vocabulary. Do NOT strip chemistry identity words as noise.
   Only strip pure descriptors:
   - Strip: spec, specification, grade, ih, pharma, coa, certificate,
     analysis, usp, nf, ep, jp, ph, eur, ip, bp, ligamed, powder,
     monograph, statement, declaration, product, information, no, number,
     material, code, batch, lot
   - Keep: any chemistry name, brand name, or molecule identifier
     (mannitol, mavacamten, croscarmellose, pearlitol, aerosil, sofosbuvir,
     velpatasvir, trilaciclib, etc.)

6. Scoring tiers must be sequential, not gated:
   Tier 1: exact normalized match → 0.99
   Tier 2: normalized candidate match → 0.99
   Tier 3: family alias match (existing logic) → 0.97
   Tier 4: token containment → 0.90
   Tier 5: token overlap (Jaccard + distinctive weighting) → 0.50-0.85
   Tier 6: filename inference match → 0.85
   Fall through to next tier if current returns below 0.90. Never short-circuit
   at 0 because family is missing.

7. Auto-accept threshold: 0.85 (was 0.45 in RS, which is too strict for good
   token matches).

8. Add product-agnostic normalization utilities. These help ANY molecule
   without requiring pre-registration:
   - Salt suffix stripper: "Trilaciclib 2HCl" → base name "trilaciclib" +
     alias "2hcl". Do same for HCl, HBr, sulfate, phosphate, acetate,
     citrate, tartrate, mesylate, tosylate, besylate, hydrochloride.
   - Hydrate suffix stripper: "Citric acid monohydrate" → base "citric acid"
     + alias "monohydrate". Do same for anhydrous, dihydrate, trihydrate,
     tetrahydrate, pentahydrate, heptahydrate, hemihydrate.
   - Purity/quality descriptor stripper: "Pyrogen Free", "Anhydrous",
     "Endotoxin-Controlled", "Sterile", "USP-NF" etc. become weak aliases,
     not identity tokens.
   - Brand-in-parentheses parser: "Mannitol (Pearlitol 50C)" →
     primary=mannitol, brand=pearlitol 50c. Both go into token pool.

9. Add these DEG/EG and RS synonym families for common excipients
